news.title: Kanpur development body launches 333 plots through auction
news.para: According to KDA, the plots are available in Mahaveer Nagar Extension, Shatabdi Nagar Scheme, Swarn Jayanti Vihar and Bhagirathi-Janhvi Nagar schemes.

news.title: Real estate projects becoming unviable due to high construction, capital cost: Tata Realty MD & CEO
news.para: When asked about the factors making projects unviable, Dutt pointed out, "Real estate requires a lot of capital in India, first of all to acquire land. In major cities such as NCR, Mumbai and Bengaluru, it (land cost) is almost 50 per cent to 80-85 per cent of the project cost."

news.title: Telangana HC stays single-judge order on Ramky Integrated Township, relief for HMDA
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice Ujjal Bhuyan and Justice N Tukaramji was hearing an appeal of HMDA which contended that the single judge order would harm its interests.

news.title: Jaypee insolvency: NCLT may pass judgement on Suraksha bid on March 7
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Jaypee Infratech Ltd informed that the matter is "further listed for order(s)/appropriate directions before Hon'ble National Company Law Tribunal, Principal Bench, New Delhi on 7th March 2023."

news.title: UK's Home REIT says two tenant firms enter voluntary liquidation
news.para: The housing provider for the homeless said Gen Liv UK CIC and Lotus Sanctuary CIC have entered into voluntary liquidation and the company was in talks with prospective tenants to take on new leases for the two portfolios.

news.title: Housing minister asks officials to revisit provision of Act to ensure no metro properties can be attached
news.para: ​The noting was made by Puri in the document attached in an additional affidavit filed by the Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs in the Delhi High Court on March 3.

news.title: Don't finalise draft DP for Pune metropolitan region without court nod: Bombay HC
news.para: The petitioners' counsel Neeta Karnik seeking interim relief said the draft DP has been prepared by the Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) through a ‘Pune Metropolitan Planning Committee’ not constituted correctly under the constitutional provisions as elected members were not its members.

news.title: Power bills to help trace new property taxpayers in Chandigarh
news.para: ​The UT has sent over 2 lakh power connections data to the civic body authority, who are currently having power connection and consuming electricity on a regular basis.

news.title: Mangaluru development body to distribute sites in Kunjathbail at Rs 8.5 lakh per cent
news.para: Muda has developed 208 sites on 17.5 acres at Kunjathbail, located about 12km from the city. While the authority will allot 182 sites by lottery, the corner sites will be auctioned, said Muda chairman Ravishankar Mijar.

news.title: Indore administration serves last notice to developers of three private colonies
news.para: Accepting the district administration’s ‘formula’ to provide relief to around 250 plot buyers of aforesaid three private colonies, the apex court had in November 2021 granted bails to the developers/colonizers, who were confined in local jail to settle accounts with the victims they had allegedly duped through different means.

news.title: Greater Noida: Guards removed, residents of JKG Palm Court raise security concern
news.para: The protesters placed five portraits of Yogi Adityanath on chairs outside the towers of JKG Palm Court society and appealed to the CM to look into their complaints.

news.title: Pfizer sells leasehold rights of 54-acre land parcel in Thane to Vidhi Research
news.para: Along with this leasehold land parcel in Turbhe, built-up areas of over 3.92 lakh sq ft including pharmaceutical manufacturing unit, warehouses, and other structures constructed over the plot have been transferred.

news.title: HSPCB's closure orders for two realty projects in Panipat flouting norms haunts buyers
news.para: All this came to light when Panipat deputy commissioner Sushil Sarwan urged the chairman of HSPCB to withdraw the orders on a representation made by harried residents on Friday.

news.title: Bank of Baroda reduces home loan rate by 40 bps to 8.5% until March 31
news.para: Both offers are with effect from March 5, 2023, and are valid for a limited period till March 31, 2023, BoB said in a statement. This is one of the lowest and most competitive interest rates in the industry, the bank claimed.

news.title: Lapsed building projects haunt Mumbai homebuyers
news.para: Especially since the city has innumerable tragic stories of families who paid tens of lakhs or even crores to book flats but have been unable to take possession of their homes for years.
